Source: mod-rpaf-fork
Section: httpd
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Kentaro YOSHIDA <y.ken.studio@gmail.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), apache2-dev, dh-apache2
Standards-Version: 4.6.0
Homepage: https://github.com/y-ken/mod_rpaf

Package: libapache2-mod-rpaf-fork
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, apache2
Description: reverse proxy add forward module for Apache (fork)
 mod_rpaf-fork sets REMOTE_ADDR, HTTPS and HTTP_PORT from the headers a reverse
 proxy adds (X-Forwarded-For, X-Forwarded-Proto, X-Forwarded-Port), so backend
 Apache sees the real client instead of the proxy.
 .
 This fork builds and runs on both Apache 2.2 and Apache 2.4 and adds
 RPAFsetport, partial-IP RPAFproxy_ips and several proxy-handling fixes.
